frame0.consensus_text: The Scots Lres further advize that on <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> 29<sw-sup>th</sw-sup> past <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> L<sw-ex>ord</sw-ex> Chancellor
delivered in 2 memorialls to the Parliam<sw-ex>en</sw-ex>t one for an Act to
Regulate Inferior Courts in that Kingdom, p<sw-ex>ar</sw-ex>ticularly <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Comissary Court
<brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> other that they would take into Consideration <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> security of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Church
& Religion, w<sw-ex>hi</sw-ex><sl>ch</sl> were Committed to a Committee -
The Berkly Castle a vast rich ship from <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> streights soe much discoursd of to be lost, is
now put into Rye in Sussex - This day Mr Gellibrand <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Messenger seizd a Cart Loade of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl>
late Kings declarac<sw-ex>i</sw-ex>ons & other Pamphletts & br<sw-ex>ough</sw-ex>t <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>e</sw-ex><sl>m</sl> to Whitehall, & one of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> accomplices
lately taken belongd to <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Printers <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>a</sw-ex><sl>t</sl> were seizd last weeke & he has made a full
discours of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Whole Matter, on w<sw-ex>hi</sw-ex><sl>ch</sl> warrants are gone abroad to take up sev<sw-ex>era</sw-ex>ll
The Plymouth Lres further say <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>a</sw-ex><sl>t</sl>
<brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Bridgett Gally hath brought ord<sw-ex>er</sw-ex>s for Provisions
& oth<sw-ex>er</sw-ex> necessaries to be sent to <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Grand ffleet
at Bell Isles from whence tis Conjectured,
they having soe many men on board, <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>a</sw-ex><sl>t</sl> they
will make some attempt upon <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> French
in that Island -
Dartmouth 2<sw-sup>d</sw-sup> <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Transport shipps
are sailed hence for Plymouth having taken
on board a Considerable Quantity of Bread -
On Saturday on Howard a Groc<sw-sup>r</sw-sup>
in Brooke street & his Brother in Grayes Inn
Lane were taken into Custody of a Messing<sw-sup><sw-unclear>?</sw-unclear></sw-sup>
an act of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Treasonable declaracon soe <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>a</sw-ex><sl>t</sl> there
is now 11 in Custody of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>a</sw-ex><sl>t</sl> Gang & search is made
after sev<sw-ex>era</sw-ex>ll others, & some are s<sw-ex>ai</sw-ex>d to be fled into
Ireland -
A Turners wife neare Lincolns
Inn ffeilds is bro<sw-ex>ugh</sw-ex>t to Towne in Custody of
a Messinger being said last weeke at
Bottom wherein were sevll L<sw-ex>ett</sw-ex>res w<sw-ex>hi</sw-ex><sl>ch</sl> she
brt from ffrance by way of fflanders -
On Saturday Anderton <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Printer
being Indicted for H<sw-ex>igh</sw-ex> Treason in printing
& disp<sw-ex>er</sw-ex>sing 35 sev<sw-ex>era</sw-ex>ll defamatory Libells
ag<sw-ex>ain</sw-ex>st <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Gover<sw-ex>n</sw-ex>m<sw-ex>en</sw-ex>t & uttering scandalous
words ag<sw-ex>ain</sw-ex>st <sw-ex>thei</sw-ex>re Ma<sw-ex>ies</sw-ex><sl>tie</sl>s after he had
Challenged 35 of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Jury was br<sw-ex>ough</sw-ex>t in
Guilty of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Treason in <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Indictment, but
did not receive sentence, <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> sessions
at <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Old Bayly being Adiourned
to Thursday next, at w<sw-ex>hi</sw-ex><sl>ch</sl> tyme Cannon
<brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Booksell<sw-sup>r</sw-sup> & dorm<sw-ex>er</sw-ex> <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> fflatter will be
tryed for disp<sw-ex>er</sw-ex>sing K. James Declarac<sw-ex>i</sw-ex>ons
as also 3 oth<sw-ex>e</sw-ex>rs who were seizd <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Close
of last weeke at douglass s <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Quakers
in <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Hay Markett, there being very
Cleare & substantiall proofe ag<sw-sup>st</sw-sup> <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>e</sw-ex><sl>m</sl> <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>a</sw-ex><sl>t</sl> they
had printed & disp<sw-ex>er</sw-ex>sed <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> late Kings decla
ffalmouth 1<sw-sup>st</sw-sup> inst<sw-ex>ant</sw-ex> since <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> 29<sw-sup>th</sw-sup>
past <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> ffr<sw-ex>ench</sw-ex> Privateers have taken 1<sw-unclear>? </sw-unclear>
Colliers coming from Wales but 4 of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>e</sw-ex><sl>m</sl>
are retaken & brt into Penzance
Yesterday 2 small Vessells were Chased
ashoare neare <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Lizard by 2 ffr<sw-ex>ench</sw-ex> Privateers
Yesterday <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Hamburgh
Envoy had Audience of her Ma<sw-ex>ies</sw-ex><sl>ty</sl>
Yesterday a notorious High
way man was seizd in <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Stocks Markett
& Committed to Newgate -
are retaken & br<sw-ex>ough</sw-ex>t into Penzance --
a Messinger being seiz<sw-ex>e</sw-ex>d last weeke at
on acc<sw-ex>oun</sw-ex>t of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Treasonable declarac<sw-ex>i</sw-ex>on, soe <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>a</sw-ex><sl>t</sl> there
